        Table manager dialog class constructor
        Parameters:
        ccddMain - main class
        dialogType - table manager dialog type: NEW, EDIT, RENAME, COPY, DELETE, IMPORT, EXPORT_CSV, EXPORT_XTCE, EXPORT_EDS, EXPORT_JSON
        callingEditorDialog - reference to the table editor dialog that instantiated this table manager. Only used when called to open a table in, import into, or export from an existing editor; null otherwise

    • Method Detail

      • doTableOperationComplete

        protected void doTableOperationComplete()
        Perform the steps needed following execution of a table management operation

      • initialize

        private void initialize()
        Create the table manager dialog. This is executed in a separate thread since it can take a noticeable amount time to complete, and by using a separate thread the GUI is allowed to continue to update. The GUI menu commands, however, are disabled until the telemetry scheduler initialization completes execution

        Create the table tree selection panel
        Parameters:
        labelText - label to display above the table tree
        gbc - GridBagLayout layout constraints
        tableSelect - table tree item selection model
        treeType - table tree type: PROTOTYPE_ONLY to show only the prototype tables, INSTANCE_ONLY to show only the table instances (parent tables with child tables), or BOTH to show the prototypes and instances
        Returns:
        JPanel containing the selection panel
